C + \frac{C}{x} + \frac{C}{x^2} + \frac{C}{x^3} +\cdots
C
\sum_{n\ge 0}\frac{C}{x^n}=C\sum_{n\ge 0}\left(\frac1x\right)^n=C\frac1{1-\frac1x}=\frac{Cx}{x-1}\;,
\left|\frac1x\right|<1
|x|>1
|x|>1
1/x
\frac{C}{1-(1/x)} = \frac{C x}{x-1}
S
S/x+C=S
S=\frac{Cx}{x-1}
S=\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{x^n}{n}
S'=\sum_{n=0}^\infty x^n
S'-1=xS'
S'=\frac{1}{1-x}
S=-\ln(1-x)
